text: Fallis is a town in the U.S. state of Oklahoma. ==Demographics== As of the census of 2020, there were 21 people, 10 households, and 7 families living in the town. The population density was 61 people per square mile (24/km2). There were 10 houses. The racial makeup of the town was 57.1% White (non-Hispanic), 23.8% two or more races (non-Hispanic), and 19.0% Hispanic or Latino. == References == Category:Towns in Oklahoma
title: Fallis, Oklahoma
